"{\"abstract\":\"We propose an end-to-end network for visual illustration of a sequence of sentences forming a story. At the core of our model is the ability to model the inter-related nature of the sentences within a story, as well as the ability to learn coherence to support reference resolution. The framework takes the form of an encoder-decoder architecture, where sentences are encoded using a hierarchical two-level sentence-story GRU, combined with an encoding of coherence, and sequentially decoded using a predicted feature representation into a consistent illustrative image sequence. We optimize all parameters of our network in an end-to-end fashion with respect to order embedding loss, encoding entailment between images and sentences. Experiments on the VIST storytelling dataset [9] highlight the importance of our algorithmic choices and efficacy of our overall model.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"39936314\",\"name\":\"Hareesh Ravi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/39936314\"},{\"authorId\":\"2670195\",\"name\":\"L. Wang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2670195\"},{\"authorId\":\"46626969\",\"name\":\"Carlos Mu\\u00f1iz\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/46626969\"},{\"authorId\":\"144398147\",\"name\":\"L. Sigal\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144398147\"},{\"authorId\":\"1711560\",\"name\":\"D. Metaxas\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1711560\"},{\"authorId\":\"143980996\",\"name\":\"Mubbasir Kapadia\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/143980996\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"50343714\",\"name\":\"Yusuke Mori\"},{\"authorId\":\"25509090\",\"name\":\"H. Yamane\"},{\"authorId\":\"2374364\",\"name\":\"Yusuke Mukuta\"},{\"authorId\":\"1790553\",\"name\":\"T. Harada\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\",\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"9cde2336a05bd2aae4522c4